A Zimmerman man yesterday was charged with assaulting his wife on Valentine&rsquo;s Day for asking why he had lipstick on his cheek.According to police records, Blench Ndegwa said nothing when Donald Maina, 28, confronted her after she asked him about the kiss mark.They both left their Zimmerman house but Maina confronted Ndegwa as she was speaking to a neighbour and started beating her, police said. &ldquo;Why are you telling people about everything in our house? And why [did you ask] about the mark on [my] cheek?&rdquo; Maina reportedly asked.Neighbours restrained him and called the police.Maina denied the charge before senior principal magistrate Angelo Kithinji and was released on Sh20,000 bail. The hearing will be on June 12.